# Deployment — Vercel

This project is deployed on **Vercel** at `https://p99scryingpool.vercel.app/`.
The GitHub repo is `ahetu/p99-scrying-pool`.

## Before committing

Run `npm run build` locally and confirm it exits cleanly (exit code 0). TypeScript type errors will fail the Vercel build silently — the old deployment stays live and no error is surfaced to the user.

## After pushing

Check that the Vercel deployment succeeded:

```
gh api repos/ahetu/p99-scrying-pool/deployments --jq ".[0] | {sha: .sha[0:7], created: .created_at, env: .environment}"
gh api repos/ahetu/p99-scrying-pool/deployments/<id>/statuses --jq ".[0] | {state, description}"
```

If `state` is `"failure"`, inspect the build logs:

```
npx vercel inspect <deployment_id> --logs
```

## Common pitfalls

- **Type mismatches in scripts/**: The scraper and enrichment scripts under `scripts/` import `ItemData` from `src/lib/types.ts`. When new fields are added to `ItemData`, **every file that constructs an `ItemData` object must be updated** — including scraper scripts, enrichment scripts, and `src/lib/wikiItemLookup.ts`. The build will fail on the type check otherwise.
- **Stale API responses**: API routes that return dynamic data must export `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic";` to prevent Vercel edge caching from serving stale results.
- **Railway is defunct**: The project previously used Railway. Ignore Railway deployment statuses in the GitHub deployments API — they will always show `"failure"`.
